1 YoLov8

This notebook explore inferencing Yolov8 on Zenbook 13 UX331UN

1.1 Environment Setup

Assuming your are on Windows 11:

  • prepare python virtual environment
  • using cuda 11.8 + cudnn 8.6
  • install pip install torch==2.0.0+cu118 torchvision==0.15.1+cu118 torchaudio==2.0.1 --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu118
  • install pip install ultralytics py-cpuinfo opencv-python pillow matplotlib
  • download suitable pre-trained model from here

def box_label(image, box, label='', color=(128, 128, 128), txt_color=(255, 255, 255)):
  lw = max(round(sum(image.shape) / 2 * 0.003), 2)
  p1, p2 = (int(box[0]), int(box[1])), (int(box[2]), int(box[3]))
  cv2.rectangle(image, p1, p2, color, thickness=lw, lineType=cv2.LINE_AA)
  if label:
    tf = max(lw - 1, 1)  # font thickness
    w, h = cv2.getTextSize(label, 0, fontScale=lw / 3, thickness=tf)[0]  # text width, height
    outside = p1[1] - h >= 3
    p2 = p1[0] + w, p1[1] - h - 3 if outside else p1[1] + h + 3
    cv2.rectangle(image, p1, p2, color, -1, cv2.LINE_AA)  # filled
    cv2.putText(image,
                label, (p1[0], p1[1] - 2 if outside else p1[1] + h + 2),
                0,
                lw / 3,
                txt_color,
                thickness=tf,
                lineType=cv2.LINE_AA)
